dc_description_s: This datset is an extration from the 2014 Pa. historic resources and structures file prepared by the Pa. Historical and Museum Commission (PHMC) . The original file contained information on 7,721 resource listings within Chester County that had been submitted to the Bureau and incorporated into their Bureau of Historic Preservation database. The files identified each resource by one of the following designations:  National Historic Landmark (8 structures and 1 District)  Structure or District listed on the National Register (246 structures and 46 districts)  Structure or District eligible for the National Register (200 structures and 21 districts)  Structure or District ineligible for the National Register (271 structures)  Undetermined (6,928 resources) This file is a subset of the original which includes any National Landmark or resource Listed on or Eligible for the National Register that Chester County Planning Commission staff could identify and verify in conjunction with County Land Records information. The file includes each of the designated resources that could be placed on the correct parcel (excluding District boundaries).
